🔥Provisioner kya hai?
👉 Provisioner = jo external system me actual action karta hai
🧠 Simple line:-
👉 User ko create / update / delete karne wala engine
🔥 Real Meaning:-
Jab tu bolta hai:-
User banao
Role assign karo
Access hatao
👉 Ye sab kaam Provisioner karta hai.

()Provisioner ek execution engine hai jo provisioning plan ko run karke external systems me user access create/update/delete karta hai.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 Provisioner kya karta hai?
✅ 1. Account Create:-
👉 External system me user banata hai
Create user in SAP / AD

✅ 2. Account Update:-
👉 User ka data change karta hai
email update
role change

✅ 3. Account Delete / Disable:-
👉 User ko remove ya disable karta hai

✅ 4. Entitlement Assign/Remove:-
👉 Roles/groups deta ya hataata hai

✅ 5. Provisioning Plan execute karta hai:-
👉 Ye sab directly nahi hota
👉 Pehle ProvisioningPlan banta hai

🔥🔹Provisioning Flow:-
Request → ProvisioningPlan → Provisioner → Connector → External System
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 Provisioner ke andar kya hota hai?
🔹 1. ProvisioningPlan
👉 Kya action lena hai
create
update
delete

🔹 2. AccountRequest
👉 Kis user pe action

🔹 3. AttributeRequest
👉 Kya change karna hai
email change
role add

🔹 4. Connector
👉 External system se connect

🔹 5. Rules (Optional)
👉 Custom logic

🔹 6. Result / Status
👉 Success / Failure
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 Example (Real Code Style):-
ProvisioningPlan plan = new ProvisioningPlan();

AccountRequest accReq = new AccountRequest();
accReq.setApplication("SAP");
accReq.setOperation(AccountRequest.Operation.Create);

AttributeRequest attr = new AttributeRequest();
attr.setName("email");
attr.setValue("rahul@gmail.com");

accReq.add(attr);
plan.add(accReq);

Provisioner provisioner = new Provisioner(context);
provisioner.execute(plan);
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 Kya DB me store hota hai?
👉 Direct Provisioner object store nahi hota ❌
--------------------------------------------------------
🔥 1️⃣ Constructor:-

✅ Provisioner(SailPointContext context):-
👉 Provisioner object banata hai
Provisioner provisioner = new Provisioner(context);
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 2️⃣ Main Execution Method:-

✅ execute(ProvisioningPlan plan):-
👉 Sabse important method,
👉 Plan ko run karta hai.
provisioner.execute(plan);
👉 Kya karta hai:-
Account create/update/delete
Entitlements assign/remove

✅ executeWithResult(ProvisioningPlan plan):-
👉 Execute + result return karta hai
ProvisioningResult result = provisioner.executeWithResult(plan);
👉 Output:-
Success / Failure
Error details

✅ compile(ProvisioningPlan plan):-
👉 Plan ko ProvisioningProject me convert karta hai
ProvisioningProject project = provisioner.compile(plan);

✅ retry(ProvisioningProject project):-
provisioner.retry(project);
👉 Failed provisioning ko dobara try karta hai.

✅ getResult():-
ProvisioningResult result = provisioner.getResult();
👉 Last execution ka result deta hai.
-----------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ compile(plan, boolean expand):-
👉 ProvisioningPlan ko execution-ready structure (ProvisioningProject) me convert karta hai.

🔹 1️⃣ Plan ko Application-wise todta hai
Ek plan me multiple applications ho sakte hain (SAP, AD, DB etc.)
compile() unhe separate karta hai

👉 Example:-
User ko:
- AD me account banana hai
- SAP me role assign karna hai

➡️ compile karega:-
AD Task
SAP Task

🔹 2️⃣ Requests ko group karta hai:-
Same application ke operations ko ek group me daal deta hai
👉 Example:-
AD me:-
- Create account
- Add to group
- Set password
➡️ Ek hi execution unit banega:-
AD Provisioning Task

🔹 3️⃣ Execution order set karta hai:-
Sabse critical part 👇
Pehle account create
Fir entitlement/role assign
👉 Galat order nahi hone deta ❌
Example:-
❌ Role assign before account creation (ERROR)
✅ Account create → then role assign

🔹 4️⃣ Dependencies handle karta hai:-
Agar ek kaam dusre pe depend hai → order fix karega
👉 Example:-
Account create → then email enable

🔹 5️⃣ expand = true ka role (🔥 hidden magic):-
Agar expand = true:-
👉 System:-
Roles ko tod deta hai individual entitlements me
Policy expansion karta hai
👉 Example:-
Role: "Manager"
➡️ Expand hone ke baad:-
- Read access
- Write access
- Approve access

🔹 6️⃣ ProvisioningProject banata hai:-
Final output 👇
ProvisioningProject project

Iske andar hota hai:-
Application wise tasks
Execution steps
Dependencies
Order

🧠 Example:-
👉 Output (Realistic Structure Example)
ProvisioningProject {
  
  plans = [
    
    AccountRequest {
      application = "Active Directory"
      operation = CREATE
      
      attributeRequests = [
        AttributeRequest {
          name = "sAMAccountName"
          value = "rahul"
          operation = SET
        },
        AttributeRequest {
          name = "password"
          value = "Pass@123"
          operation = SET
        }
      ]
      
      entitlementRequests = [
        EntitlementRequest {
          name = "memberOf"
          value = "CN=Employees,OU=Groups,DC=company,DC=com"
          operation = ADD
        }
      ]
    },

    AccountRequest {
      application = "SAP"
      operation = MODIFY
      
      entitlementRequests = [
        EntitlementRequest {
          name = "role"
          value = "Z_MANAGER"
          operation = ADD
        }
      ]
    }

  ]
}
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥(2)expandPlan(ProvisioningPlan plan):-
ProvisioningPlan expandedPlan = provisioner.expandPlan(plan);
👉 Simple ek line me:-
👉 High-level access(Role,Policy,Bundle) → actual entitlements (permissions/groups) me convert karta hai.

🧠 Real me problem kya hoti hai?
👉 User ko directly permission nahi dete, hum dete hain:-
Role = "Manager"
❌ Problem:-
System ko nahi pata "Manager" ka matlab kya hai execution ke time

🔥 expandPlan kya karta hai?
👉 "Manager" ko tod deta hai actual cheezon me:-
- AD Group: Managers
- SAP Role: Z_MANAGER
- Email Access: Enabled
👉 ab system ko clear ho gaya kya karna hai.

👉 “Manager” ko 3 items me kyu toda?
👉 Kyunki “Manager” ek single role nahi hota,
ye actually ek bundle/collection of permissions hota hai.
aur jar permission/access aek item/certificationitem/accessrequestitem hota hai.

()1 role = multiple systems ka access:-
🔹 1️⃣ AD Group: Managers:-
👉 Identity system (Active Directory) me access
Login / authentication
Group-based permissions

🔹 2️⃣ SAP Role: Z_MANAGER:-
👉 Business system (SAP) me access
Reports
Transactions
Business operations

🔹 3️⃣ Email Access: Enabled:-
👉 Communication system me access
Email send/receive
Outlook access


----------------------
🧠 Internally kya karta hai expand?
🔹 1️⃣ Role → Entitlements convert
Role ko todta hai multiple permissions me:-
👉 Input Plan:-
Role = "Manager"
➡️ expandPlan karega:-
Entitlements:-
- Read Access
- Write Access
- Approve Access

🔹 2️⃣ Policy / Rule Expansion:-
Agar koi policy ya rule laga hai
toh usko bhi expand karta hai
👉 Example:-
Policy: "Finance Role"
➡️ Expand:-
- SAP_FIN_READ
- SAP_FIN_WRITE


(3)Application Mapping kya hota hai?
👉 expandPlan() ke time par system decide karta hai:-
“kaunsa entitlement kis application (AD, SAP, Email, etc.) me apply hoga”

👉 Input (User ka Role):-
Role: "Manager"
👉 System me mapping defined hai (IMPORTANT):-
Role	   Application	   Entitlement
Manager	      AD	       CN=Managers
Manager	      SAP	       Z_MANAGER
Manager 	Exchange	   Mailbox Enabled
Manager	   File Server	   Shared Folder Access

🔥 expandPlan ka OUTPUT (Actual Mapping):-
ProvisioningPlan {
  🔹 Active Directory (AD)
  AccountRequest:
    Entitlement:
      - memberOf = CN=Managers,OU=Groups,DC=company,DC=com

  🔹 SAP System
  AccountRequest:
    Entitlement:
      - role = Z_MANAGER

  🔹 Email System (Exchange)
  AccountRequest:
    Attribute:
      - mailboxEnabled = true

  🔹 File Server
  AccountRequest:
    Entitlement:
      - access = SharedFolder_Manager

}

🔹 4️⃣ Hidden dependencies add karta hai
Jaise:-
Mailbox create
Default groups

🔥 Hidden Dependencies kya hoti hain?
👉 Ye aise required actions / permissions hain jo directly plan me nahi likhe hote,
lekin system unhe automatically add ya trigger karta hai taaki provisioning sahi se ho sake.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 3️⃣ provision(ProvisioningProject project):-
provisioner.provision(project);
👉 Kya karta hai?
👉 Actual execution karta hai (no result return)

🔍 Internally:-
Connector call karta hai
External system me changes karta hai

👉 Output:-
❌ Return nahi karta
👉 Bas execute karta hai
------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 4️⃣ provisionWithResult(ProvisioningProject project):-
ProvisioningResult result = provisioner.provisionWithResult(project);
👉 Kya karta hai?

👉 Execute + result deta hai

🔍 Output:-
Success / Failure
Error message
Status per account
---------------------------------
✅ provisionIdentity(Identity identity):-
provisioner.provisionIdentity(identity);
👉 Kya karta hai?
👉 Identity ke pending changes ko apply karta hai

🔍 Internally:-
Identity ke roles check karta hai
Required access calculate karta hai
Plan generate karta hai
Execute karta hai

🧠 Example:-
👉 Identity me role add kiya →
👉 Ye method automatically:-
group assign karega
account update karega
---------------------------------------
✅ provisionIdentityWithResult(Identity identity):-
ProvisioningResult result = provisioner.provisionIdentityWithResult(identity);
👉 Same upar ka kaam + result return
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ setTrace(true):-
provisioner.setTrace(true);
👉 Kya karta hai?
👉 Detailed logs ON karta hai
🧠 Output:-
Connecting to SAP...
Executing create account...
Success
------------------------------------------------
🔥 1️⃣ simulate(ProvisioningPlan plan):-
ProvisioningResult result = provisioner.simulate(plan);
👉 Simple Meaning:-
👉 Plan ko execute kiye bina sirf test karta hai

🧠 Kya karta hai internally?
Check karta hai:-
Kya plan valid hai?
Kya permissions mil sakti hain?
Koi error to nahi aayega?
Real system me kuch change nahi karta ❌

💥 Real Output (Example):-
ProvisioningResult:-
- Status: SUCCESS
- Warnings: None
- Errors: None
Simulated Actions:-
- AD: Group "Managers" add (OK)
- SAP: Role "Z_MANAGER" assign (OK)
- Email: Mailbox enable (OK)
-------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 2️⃣ setNoLocking(true):-
provisioner.setNoLocking(true);
👉 Simple Meaning:-
👉 Locking mechanism ko disable kar deta hai

🧠 Locking kya hota hai?
👉 Normally:-
Same user pe ek time me ek hi provisioning process chale

👉 Locking ka kaam:-
Race condition avoid karna
Data corruption rokna

💥 No Locking = kya hoga?
👉 Agar tu true karta hai:-
Multiple provisioning processes ek sath chal sakte hain
Lock nahi lagega
⚠️ Risk:-
- Data conflict
- Duplicate provisioning
- Inconsistent state

⚡ Use case:-
👉 Jab:-
High performance chahiye
Parallel processing karna hai
External system already handle kar raha ho.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 3️⃣ setOptimisticProvisioning(true):-
provisioner.setOptimisticProvisioning(true);
👉 Simple Meaning:-
👉 System bina wait kiye assume karta hai ki provisioning SUCCESS hogi

🧠 Normal(Optimistic OFF) vs Optimistic ON:-
✅ Normal Mode (default):-
User → request send
   ↓
System → provisioning complete hone ka wait karega
   ↓
Success/Failure response
👉 yaha system confirm karke hi response deta hai

✅ Optimistic Mode (true):-
User → request send
   ↓
System → "OK SUCCESS" bol deta hai
   ↓
Actual provisioning background me hoti hai
👉 yaha system jaldi response de deta hai (fast UX).
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
💥 Real Example:-
👉 Scenario:-
User ko role assign karna hai:-
Role = Manager
🔹 Optimistic = TRUE

👉 System response:-
Status: SUCCESS

👉 But actual:-
- AD Group add (pending)
- SAP role assign (pending)
- Email enable (pending)
👉 sab background me chal raha hai

⚠️ Agar failure ho gaya?
👉 Response already SUCCESS de chuka hai 😬
👉 Later:-
- Provisioning failed
- Retry required
