💥 PlanExecutor kya karta hai?
👉 Ye actual work karta hai:-
- Account create
- Role assign
- Attribute update

🔥 1️⃣ setPlanExecutor(PlanExecutor executor):-
provisioner.setPlanExecutor(executor);
👉 Simple Meaning:-
👉 Kaunsa engine / logic plan ko execute karega — ye set karta hai

🧠 Kya hota hai internally?
👉 Provisioning system me:-
Compile → Plan banta hai
Execute → PlanExecutor karta hai
👉 Tu yaha execution ka control de raha hai.

🔥 Custom behavior:-
👉 Tu apna custom executor bana sakta hai:-
public class MyPlanExecutor implements PlanExecutor {
    public void execute(ProvisioningPlan plan) {
        // custom logic
    }
}
👉 fir set:-
provisioner.setPlanExecutor(new MyPlanExecutor());
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 2️⃣ addExceptionListener(...):-
provisioner.addExceptionListener(listener);
👉 Simple Meaning:-
👉 Jab provisioning me error aaye, usko handle karne ke liye listener add karta hai

🧠 Exception Listener kya karta hai?
👉 Ye error ko catch karke handle karta hai

💥 Example:-
provisioner.addExceptionListener(new ExceptionListener() {
    public void handleException(Exception e) {
        System.out.println("Error occurred: " + e.getMessage());
    }
});
🔥 Kya hota hai jab error aata hai?
Provisioning → Error aaya
        ↓
ExceptionListener trigger
        ↓
Custom handling (log / alert / retry)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContextFactory;
import sailpoint.object.ProvisioningPlan;
import sailpoint.provisioning.Provisioner;
import sailpoint.tools.ExceptionListener;

public class StandaloneDemo {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        try {
            // ⚠️ Ye tabhi chalega jab IdentityIQ environment ho
            SailPointContextFactory factory = new SailPointContextFactory();
            SailPointContext context = factory.getContext();

            Provisioner provisioner = new Provisioner(context);

            provisioner.addExceptionListener(new ExceptionListener() {
                public void handleException(Exception e) {
                    System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
                }
            });

            ProvisioningPlan plan = new ProvisioningPlan();

            provisioner.compile(plan, true);

        } catch (Exception e) {
            System.out.println("❌ Standalone me error aayega:");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
❌ Case 3: ExceptionListener ka error
🔹 Error:
Error: Provisioning failed: Missing account
📍 Ye error kis line se aata hai?

👉 Is block se:-
provisioner.addExceptionListener(new ExceptionListener() {
    public void handleException(Exception e) {
        System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
    }
});
🧠 Important:-
👉 Ye error throw nahi karta
👉 Ye sirf print karta hai

👉 Actual flow:-
Provisioner ke andar koi error aata hai
ExceptionListener call hota hai
Ye line execute hoti hai:-
System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
🧠 Example:-
Agar provisioning fail hua:-
👉 Output:-
Error: Missing account
-----------------------------------------------------------------
❌ Case 1: NoClassDefFoundError / ClassNotFoundException
🔹 Error:-
java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: sailpoint/api/SailPointContextFactory
Caused by: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException

🔹 Ye kahan se aata hai?
👉 Is line par:-
SailPointContextFactory factory = new SailPointContextFactory();

🔹 Matlab kya hai?
👉 Java ko SailPointContextFactory class mil hi nahi rahi ❌

🔹 Simple meaning:-
“Tumne jis class ko use karne ki koshish ki hai, wo class tumhare classpath me exist hi nahi karti.”

🔹 Reason (kyu hota hai?)
❌ 1. SailPoint JAR add nahi kiya
👉 IdentityIQ ke required .jar files project me include nahi hai

❌ 2. Classpath me missing hai
👉 JVM ko pata hi nahi hai ki class kaha hai
/////*👉 Classpath = Java ko batane wala path jahan se wo classes (.class files) aur JAR files dhoondta hai.
🔹IDE me (Eclipse / IntelliJ):-
🔸Eclipse me:-
Right click project → Build Path
→ Configure Build Path
→ Libraries tab

👉 Wahan tumhe:-
JAR files
external libraries
project dependencies
dikh jaati hain (ye hi classpath hota hai)*/////////

❌ 3. IdentityIQ libraries load nahi hui
👉 Required dependencies (libs) load nahi hui

❌ 4. Wrong environment
👉 Tum code standalone Java program me run kar rahe ho
👉 Par ye class sirf IdentityIQ environment me available hoti hai
--------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
❌ Case 2: Context not available (GeneralException):-
🔹 Error:-
sailpoint.tools.GeneralException: Context not available
🔹 Ye error kahan se aata hai?
👉 Is line par:-
SailPointContext context = factory.getContext();

🔹 Matlab kya hai?
👉 Class (code) mil gayi ✅
👉 Lekin IdentityIQ ka proper environment nahi mil raha ❌

🔹 Simple meaning:-
“Context tabhi milega jab IdentityIQ system properly running aur accessible ho”
🔹 Context kab milta hai? (Conditions)
✔️ 1. IdentityIQ server running ho
Application properly start hona chahiye
War deployed hona chahiye
✔️ 2. Valid session ho
User login ho
Session active ho
✔️ 3. Proper authentication ho
User authorized ho
System usko access allow kare
✔️ 4. Correct environment ho
Code IdentityIQ ke andar run ho
(jaise: rule, task, workflow)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------